node.text:
which house does pisces rule in your chart?

everybody has every sign ruling each house in their chart. if you have any doubles of 2 signs and none of others (if this case pisces) your chart is probably calculated with the default placidus system and you have an interception. 

so in order to find out which house pisces rules in your chart if you have pisces intercepted, watch my new igtv video! 

or the second option: (swipe to 4th image) (yes i’m using an old pic), go to astro-seek.com to calculate your chart, click on ‘extended settings: house system….” and change it from placidus to whole sign. 

in this example (swipe to 5th slide), gemini rules the 9th house, cancer rules the 10th house, leo rules the 11th house, virgo rules the 12th house, libra rules the 1st house, scorpio rules the 2nd house, sagittarius rules the 3rd house, capricorn rules the 4th house, aquarius rules the 5th house, pisces rules the 6th house, aries rules the 7th house, and taurus rules the 8th house!!

credit to @astrologyandlifeofficial! give them a follow, their content is neat :))

#realastrologyhouses
